{
  "texts": [
    "All three upper bounds are increasing in the automation index I t.",
    "If automation is full, Φ(I t) = 1, the upper bounds are K + t = ∞ and Y + t = ∞, and the upper bound on wages discontinuously collapses to w + t = A.",
    "Observe that for any twice continuously dierentiable period utility function that is increasing and strictly concave, the elasticity in the Euler equation (14) satises η(C t) ∈ (0, ∞).",
    "Consumption on the optimal path is increasing as long as F K > ρ + δ and constant when F K = ρ + δ.",
    "Our characterization of the factor price frontier delivers most of the remaining results."
  ]
}